{"word":"ἀπόστολος","slug":"ἀπόστολος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ἀπόστολος, ου, ὁ</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ prec.\">prec.</a>] ‘one who is sent on a mission/assignment’<b><p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp></b> general sense, <b><i>messenger, delegate</i> <a href='B:490 11:49'>Lk 11:49</a>; <a href='B:540 8:23'>2 Cor 8:23</a>; <a href='B:570 2:25'>Phil 2:25</a>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp></b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ esp.\">esp.</a> of <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ pers.\">pers.</a> of extraordinary status in the work of the gospel <b><i>ambassador, apostle, envoy:</i></b> the twelve disciples of Jesus <b><a href='B:470 10:2'>Mt 10:2</a></b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ al.\">al.</a>—Paul <b><a href='B:520 1:1'>Ro 1:1</a>; <a href='B:550 1:1'>Gal 1:1</a></b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ al.\">al.</a>—Others: Barnabas <b><a href='B:510 14:14'>Ac 14:14</a>;</b> Junia <b><a href='B:520 16:7'>Ro 16:7</a>;</b>opposition figures <b><a href='B:540 11:5'>2 Cor 11:5</a>, <a href='B:540 11:13'>13</a>; <a href='B:730 2:2'>Rv 2:2</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀποστολή\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀποστοματίζω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}